-- Sodic Jumps to 5-Month High on Medinet Nasr Bets: Cairo Mover
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-02-16T12:15:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/sodic-jumps-to-5-month-high-on-medinet-nasr-bets-cairo-mover.html
Six of October Development &
Investment Co.  surged to the highest level in five months on
speculation the Cairo-based property developer is in talks to
buy a stake in  Medinet Nasr Housing. (MNHD)   Shares of the company also known as Sodic gained for an
eighth day, climbing by the 10 percent daily limit to 15.3
Egyptian pounds, the highest intraday level since Sept. 19, at
2:01 p.m. in Cairo. The stock has soared 52 percent in eight
days. The benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  fell 0.9 percent today.  “Investors are speculating Sodic is negotiating to buy
Beltone’s stake in Medinet Nasr Housing, so shares of both
companies are moving in tandem,” said Hassan Kenawi, equity
trader at Cairo-based HC Brokerage.  Beltone Investment Group (BTFH)  holds a 23 percent stake in
Medinet Nasr Housing,  data  compiled by Bloomberg show.  Sodic and Medinet Nasr in statements to the bourse said
they had no “material news” to report. An official at Beltone
wasn’t immediately available to comment when contacted by
Bloomberg today.  Medinet Nasr gained for a fifth day, jumping 10 percent to
16.75 pounds, the highest intraday level in more than six
months. Beltone Financial Holding SAE climbed 2.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
